FBIS3-8320 "dreeu046_b_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 March 1994 BULGARIA Berov Suffers Heart Attack; Matinchev Named AU0803151594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 GMT 8 Mar 94 AU0803151594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Language: Bulgarian Article Type:BFN [Text] At the start of the news, I will repeat once again the announcement from the Council of Ministers Press Center: At 2 AM on 8 March, Prime Minister Lyuben Berov suffered a heart attack, following which he was admitted to the Lozenets Hospital of the Military Medical Academy in Sofia. After the doctors had held a consultation, it was decided that it was necessary to admit him for in-patient treatment. It was announced later that Deputy Prime Minister Evgeni Matinchev will fulfill the duties of prime minister while Professor Berov is undergoing medical treatment.
